INSERT INTO `tbl_pages_language_data` VALUES (1,'MANAGE_SHIPPING_ZONES',-1,'Shipping Zones','Manage the list of shipping zones from where users can purchase product(s) from your platform and have it shipped to them. ','Zones must be linked with Countries before setting shipping profiles.','Zones are used in creating shipping profiles that determine the final shipping charges of an order.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>View and manage all the shipping zones of the world under this module. </li>\r\n	<li>Although it is not required, you have the option to add as many shipping zones as you need to this list. To add a new shipping zone, click on New. </li>\r\n	<li>Once a zone has been added to the list, it cannot be deleted.</li>\r\n	<li>These zones come in handy while creating shipping profiles and setting shipping rates for each zone. </li>\r\n	<li>For a zone to work, it needs to be linked with a country/countries before it is linked to a shipping profile. Link countries to different zones under Settings > Countries. </li>\r\n	<li>Zone Status: Mark the current status of the zone. Only active zones will be displayed in the system.</li>\r\n	<li>System-wide impact: Editing the details (name) of an existing zone will automatically reflect in the entire system. </li>\r\n	<li>Zone not found when handling Shipping Profile? This might be because you have:\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>- Not linked any country with your zone; link countries to zones from Manage Countries.</li>\r\n			<li>- Not linked any state with the country linked to the zone. Link states to countries from Manage States.</li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n</ul> '),(2,'MANAGE_STATES',-1,'States','Manage the list of states that will be visible under any state field all over the platform','','To remove a state from the serviceable list, deactivate that state\'s entry.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Manage the list of states that will be visible under any state field all over the platform. </li>\r\n	<li> Activate or deactivate as many states as you want. Just ensure that the active states have their countries activated as well, because: If you activate the states - California and Arizona, but have deactivated the USA under Countries, these two states will not be serviceable by the platform. </li>\r\n	<li>Edit a state by clicking on the edit icon beside it.</li>\r\n	<li>You cannot delete a state from the list, although you can deactivate it if you do not want it to be visible in any of the state dropdown lists.</li>\r\n</ul> '),(3,'MANAGE_BRANDS',-1,'Brands','Manage all the brands available on the platform (ex. name, logo, and banner).','A brand will be visible at the front end only if it is linked to a product(s). ','Deactivate a brand if you do not want to use it for a specific period of time, instead of deleting it. ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Define the linking of a brand to a product as optional/mandatory under System Settings > Configuration > Product tab.</li>  \r\n	<li>Brand requests placed by sellers and accepted by you (admin) will be listed here.</li>  \r\n	<li>Brands will be visible at the front end, only if they are linked to a product(s).</li>  \r\n	<li>If a brand is not being displayed at the front end or in the brand list (to link it with a product), it might be because the product might have been marked as inactive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>     '),(4,'MANAGE_SHOPS',-1,'Shops','View and manage all the seller\'s registered shops (stores) on the platform.','Inactive shops will not be visible at front end.','View the spam reporting done for a shop by clicking on the respective shop\'s reports value. ','','\r\n<div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>View the number of products being sold under a shop, the number of reviews given, and the number of spam reports made. </li>\r\n		<li>Click on the numbers in blue to view the list and its respective details. For instance, you can view the list of products in a shop by clicking on the number of products beside the respective shop. This will direct you to a page where you can see all the product variants being sold under the shop and their inventory details.</li>\r\n		<li>Review the spam reports made for each shop by clicking on the value under Reports for the respective shop. This will direct you to the Report Shops page.</li>\r\n		<li>Each shop\'s information will be displayed on the shop\'s front end page (shop detail page) for users to view.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul></div>    '),(5,'MANAGE_CATEGORIES',-1,'Product Categories ','Set up categories to group similar products together at the front end, and make the product search easier for buyers. ','A category will be displayed at the front end, only if a product(s) has been linked to it. ','The number beside each category defines the number of products linked to it. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Make the browsing of items easier on the platform by working on the right type categorization. Add multiple categories to the platform. </li>\r\n	<li>Each category can have several subcategories.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Click on a category\'s blank section to drag and drop it and change its sequence. The same sequence is displayed on the front end and in the category list everywhere on the platform.</li>\r\n	<li>Drag and drop a category under another category, to make it a subcategory.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Each category has a number displayed beside it. This defines the number of products linked to the category and its subcategory.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul></div>\r\n<ul>  \r\n	  \r\n	<li>If you edit the details of an existing category, it will reflect automatically in the entire system. </li>\r\n	<li>If any specific category listed here is not found at the front end, this might be because:\r\n		<ul>  \r\n			<li>No product (s) is linked to the respective category.</li>    \r\n			<li>Products linked to the respective category don\'t fulfill the required conditions to get displayed at the front end. The product too won\'t be visible at the front end. Refer to the product\'s inventory details under the Seller\'s Product Inventory page, to see why the product isn\'t eligible.&nbsp;</li>  \r\n  \r\n			<li>The respective parent category or subcategory has been deleted or marked inactive.&nbsp;</li> \r\n		</ul>  </li>\r\n</ul>  '),(6,'MANAGE_BRAND_REQUEST',-1,'Brand Requests','Manage the status of the new brands requested by the sellers.','Allow sellers to add a brand directly by editing the respective settings under Settings > System Configurations > Product tab. ','Only the approved brands can be linked to any product.','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n  \r\n	<li>Once a brand request has been approved by the admin (you), the brand request is removed from this list.</li>\r\n	<li>Manage all the brands available on the platform under Product Catalog > Brands.</li>\r\n	<li>Approved and active brands can be linked to any product.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>          '),(7,'CATEGORIES_REQUESTS',-1,'Category Requests','Manage the status and details of new categories requested by sellers.','Only approved categories can be linked to products. ','','','\r\n<div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Once you (admin) approves a category request, that is when you and sellers can link products to it. </li>\r\n		<li>Once a product category has been approved, it will be removed from this list. Manage all the product categories under Product Catalog > Categories.</li>\r\n		<li>This list has only those category requests that have been rejected or that are pending approval.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul></div>          '),(8,'MANAGE_OPTIONS',-1,'Product Options','Set up different product options, such as color, size, dimensions, etc., and their respective option values like red, small, 4” x 8\", etc.','','To link a product option to a product, go to Product Catalog > Edit Product > Variant and Options Tab.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Every product you add on the platform can have different variants. For instance, you can be selling a shirt that is available in different sizes and different colors as well.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Product options include things like the size, color, brand, storage, dimensions, etc., that help distinguish similar products from one another. </li>\r\n	<li>Product options are particularly useful when you have products that are from the same category (t-shirts or mugs, for instance) but with varying characteristics, such as color, size, or logo.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>Process to Create Product Options (for a shirt available in different sizes):</div>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\">\r\n	<li>Create a product option type named \"shirt (size)”. Creating an option type means that you gave the option type a name.</li>\r\n	<li>Add the values under the option type by clicking on the Options Values icon beside it. This will direct you to the option values page, and you can add the values according. Add the values for - shirt (size) as L, M, and S.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Now, go to&nbsp;Product Catalog and when you are adding the product details, select this product option under Variants &amp; Options section. And then select all the values too. This will create all the possible product variants for the respective product.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>  '),(12,'MANAGE_TAGS',-1,'Product Tags','Add or remove keywords (Tags) corresponding to each product.','','Type a keyword or phrase and press Enter on your keyboard to make it as a tag.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tags are important as they help users search for a product much faster using the search bar.</li>\r\n	<li>It also helps the system to automatically list all the similar products for buyers to choose from.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>To create a tag, click on the field and type the keyword or phrase. Once done, press Enter on your keyboard to mark it as a tag.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Add multiple tags for each product. However, do not create spam tags as they take up the server\'s storage space.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(13,'ORDERS_OVERVIEW',-1,'Orders Details','Orders listing to view and manage its status for each seller','','','','\r\n'),(14,'MANAGE_SUBSCRIPTION_ORDERS',-1,'Subscription Orders','Manage all the sellers\' subscription orders and update their payment statuses.','Subscription orders with \"PAID\" payment status cannot be deleted.','Newly placed subscription orders always get listed at the top.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Sellers subscription module can be activated or deactivated under Settings > System Configurations > Subscription tab.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Sellers packages can be managed under Settings > Seller Subscription Packages.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Perform easy search by using different filter options provided on this page.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"> Action buttons on this page facilitate you to view the order details or delete that particular order.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n	<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />\r\n		</div>&nbsp;</div>        '),(15,'MANAGE_WITHDRAWAL_REQUESTS',-1,'Withdrawal Requests','Manage the payment status of all the Withdrawal Requests initiated by users of the platform. ','','The withdrawal requests listed here are from buyers, affiliates, advertisers and sellers. ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Set the minimum and maximum withdrawal amount limit for the users under Settings > System Configurations > User Account tab.</li>  \r\n	<li>Add comments while updating the withdrawal request status.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>        '),(16,'MANAGE_ORDER_CANCEL_REASONS',-1,'Order Cancellation Reasons','Manage the reasons that buyers can select while placing a cancellations request.','Buyers can only select the reasons you list here, and cannot add their own reason while placing a cancellation request. ','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Buyers can request for the order cancellation when the order status is - Payment Is Confirmed, In Process and also in case of Cash On Delivery.</li>\r\n	<li>The system also allows sellers to cancel orders before they are arranged for shipment by the seller.</li>\r\n	<li>There is a sorting icon provided beside the column’s header. Click on this icon to sort the list in either the ascending or descending order.</li>\r\n</ul>     '),(17,'MANAGE_ORDER_RETURN_REASONS',-1,'Order Return Reasons','Manage the reasons that buyers can select while placing a return request.','Buyers can only select the reasons you list here, and cannot add their own reason while placing a return request. ','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Buyers can request to return the order before the return period ends, and the order status has not been marked as completed.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Define the order status before which a buyer can raise a return request under Settings > System Configurations > Checkout tab.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>There is a sorting icon provided beside the column’s header. Click on this icon to sort the list in either the ascending or descending order.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),(18,'MANAGE_ORDER_STATUS',-1,'Order Status ','Manage the status of Products and Subscription Orders.','It is advised not to add more order statuses under this submodule without the help of a developer.','Edit the name and color of the order status as per your requirements. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Order statuses are used to inform buyers about the stages of an order. They are primarily used to define the current state of an order.</li>\r\n	<li>It is advised not to add more order statuses under this submodule without the help of a developer.</li>\r\n	<li>This submodule was created so that you can keep track of the statuses, edit their badge colors and so on.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>You CANNOT edit the order status priority. You will need the help of a developer for the same.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.2rem; font-family: Poppins; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\r\n	<div>Contact the Yo!Kart support team in case you want to change this list.&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div><br />\r\n		</div><br />\r\n	</h1>     '),(19,'MANAGE_ADMIN_USERS',-1,'Admin Users','Manage all the admin sub-users and assign them specific permissions based on their role. ','','A sub-user requires the \"Read & Write\" permission to add, edit or delete information in a module. ','','\r\n<div>Depending upon the permission granted, a user can view, add, edit and access a particular module.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>‘None’ means no permission has been granted.</li>\r\n	<li> ‘Read Only’ means&nbsp;permission to \'only view\' that particular module has been granted.</li>  \r\n	<li>‘Read &amp; Write’ means Sub-admin users can View/Add/Edit information.</li>\r\n</ul>      '),(20,'MANAGE_USERS',-1,'Users','View and manage all the users that register on the platform including sellers, buyers, advertisers, and affiliates. ','Every seller is automatically registered as an advertiser.','Manage the seller\'s and buyer\'s registration-related configuration under Settings > System Configurations > User Account.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Affiliate registration-related configuration can be managed under Settings > System Configuration > Affiliate.</li>  \r\n	<li>Manage every detail of the user, and even log into their account and take actions accordingly like as if you were that user.&nbsp;</li>  \r\n</ul>   '),(21,'MANAGE_USER_REWARDS',-1,'Reward Points','Credit reward points to buyers based on their on-store activities and loyalty. ','Define how many reward points equals to 1 {default currency} under Settings > System Configurations > Rewards Points.','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Define how many reward points equals to 1 {default currency} under Settings > System Configurations > Rewards Points.</li>\r\n	<li>All the reward points related settings can be managed under&nbsp;Settings > System Configurations > Rewards Points.</li>\r\n	<li>Simply use this module to appreciate your buyers whenever required through additional reward points (other than those you have set up under the rewards settings).</li>\r\n</ul> '),(22,'TRANSACTIONS',-1,'Transactions','View the list of all the wallet transactions taking place on the platform for every user.','Users cannot debit wallet amount directly. ','You (admin) can credit/debit wallet amounts for selective users.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Manage all the users\' wallet transactions from this module.</li>\r\n	<li>Users cannot directly debit amounts from their wallet. They need to place a debit request which is sent to you. Once you approve it, the amount will be debited from the respective user\'s wallet into their payment mode\'s account.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>You can credit or debit any amount, at any time for any user through this page.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>'),(23,'DELETED_USERS',-1,'Deleted Users ','Track all the deleted user from the platform and restore them when needed.','You cannot delete a user permanently from the platform.','Users who requested to truncate their data can be restored, but the user profile will not have any visible data. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NO user is permanently deleted from the platform.</li>\r\n	<li>Restore any user you want by clicking the restore icon beside it.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Users who requested to truncate their data and close their account will be listed here and can be restored. However, when you restore their account, you will not have any data in it, and their email and username will have \"xxx\" in it.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Hence, the only way for a user to truly leave the platform is when they request to truncate the data as deleting a user doesn\'t permanently delete them.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul> '),(25,'MANAGE_CURRENCIES',-1,'Currencies','Manage multiple currencies on the platform by configuring the conversion rate, symbol placement, and currency code.','All currencies, excluding the default currency, will act as currency displays for users. No transactions will take place in these currencies. ','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Add currencies to the platform and define their conversion rates. The conversion rate is defined using the default currency. </li>\r\n<li>Add as many currencies as you want to the list. These currency options will act as display currencies. </li>\r\n<li>Once a currency is added to the system, you cannot delete it. You can only update the information or deactivate it. </li>\r\n<li>Click on Sync to synchronize all the currency values once you have uploaded a new currency in the system, or updated the conversion value of an already-added currency.</li>\r\n<li>All the actual transactions take place in the Default Currency. Set the Default Currency under Settings > System Configuration > System.</li>  '),(26,'THEME_SETTINGS',-1,'Theme Settings','Update and manage the font type, size, and theme of the platform to offer a better user experience. ','','Change the theme as per your branding and preview it before finalizing.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>There are four color fields that will define the theme of the website. Click on a color box to select a different color for the theme. </li>\r\n	<li>Make sure that the inverse color selection is in contrast with the theme color.</li>\r\n	<li>Click on the font family field, and select the type of font you want. </li>\r\n	<li>Under the font-weight field, select the different font sizes that you want to use for different sections of the platform. </li>\r\n	<li>If you want to reset the changes you made, click on Reset. This will update the fields to the last saved details. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(27,'MANAGE_LABELS',-1,'Labels','Labels represent arbitrary text used with various input fields, buttons, messages (success or error), and more.','The platform offers multiple languages. Use language-specific labels appropriately.','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A label is a component that places the text in a container. It defines the object beside it. For instance, on a form, for the \"Description\" text field, \"description\" is the label. </li>\r\n	<li>Edit any label on the platform from this preconfigured list of labels that comes with the system.</li>\r\n	<li>Search for a label using the search bar at the top of the list.</li>\r\n	<li>There are two kinds of labels - web and app. </li>\r\n	<li>Update both the web application platform and mobile application platform labels by clicking on the edit icon beside them. </li>\r\n	<li>No label can be deleted from the system.</li>\r\n</ul> '),(28,'MANAGE_COMMISSIONS',-1,'Site Commission','Set the commission rate at different levels including the product level, category level, and/or seller level. ','Default commission is applicable for all the products, categories, and sellers. Users will earn a commission in the default currency.','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The commission rate in the list (Shop/ seller name, Product Categories and Product columns) with \"-\" entry is the main website commission. It doesn\'t have any conditions and it cannot be deleted. </li>\r\n	<li>Edit the overall website commission by clicking on the edit icon beside it. You can also edit the site\'s commission under Settings > System Configuration > Website Commission.</li>\r\n	<li>Customize multiple commission rates specific to a shop, a product, and/or a category. For instance, Shop A can be charged a 5% commission in addition to the overall website commission.</li>\r\n	<li>Each commission rate added will have two action icons beside them: delete to delete the commission rate and history to view the history of the commission rate changes. </li>\r\n</ul>  '),(29,'USER_ADDRESSES',-1,'Users\' Addresses','Manage all the user\'s addresses that have been added on the platform. ','','Default marked address will be auto-selected as the main address.','','\r\n'),(30,'MANAGE_USER_GDPR_REQUEST',-1,'GDPR Requests','Review and respond to GDPR request for data deletion or inquiries of where the respective user\'s data is being used. ','There is no option to decline a GDPR request.','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Yo!Kart adheres to the General Data Protection Regulation Act (GDPR) and takes it very seriously. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>This law governs the rules regarding protection and privacy rights of a user.</div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>This platform ensures that the law is followed and users feel safe sharing their information on this platform. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>This submodule gathers all the GDPR requests placed by users who want to either wipe out their personal data from this platform or learn what personal data the platform has stored, of the user.</div></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>Process:</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">For data deletion</span> - Click on the truncate data icon and the user’s data will be deleted. Note that the user’s personal details will only be deleted and the order details will not be deleted. Once done, click on the complete icon (explained below). Kindly note that everything about the user will be deleted once you delete the user\'s account from the system.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">For data retrieval</span> - Click on the view icon beside the request. Send an email with all the details saved for the respective user on their email address. Once done, click the complete icon. With this, the user will get an email about the same.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>'),(31,'SPECIAL_PRICE',-1,'Special Price','Manage and create special price offers for product variants.','At a time, only one product variant sold by a specific seller can be linked to a special price.','The special price amount of the product should fall between the minimum selling price and the selling price set by the seller. ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Volume discount and other discounts are applicable on a product\'s Special Price. This means that if the special price is $1000 (actual price is 1500), and another discount is available of 10%, then the product\'s final checkout price will be $900.<br />\r\n		</li>\r\n	<li>Special Price will be the final price for a product variant, in case there are no other discounts applicable.</li>    \r\n	<li>The special price amount of the product should fall between the minimum selling price and the selling price set by the seller.&nbsp;<br />\r\n		\r\n		<ul>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n</ul> '),(32,'VOLUME_DISCOUNT',-1,'Volume Discount','Manage and add volume (units) based discounts for product variants.','Volume discount is also applicable on products that have a special price offer running. ','','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>A volume discount involves lowering the price of the product when increased quantities of a product are purchased. </li>\r\n	<li>For instance, create a volume discount offer on a product where a 10% discount is applied when the minimum purchase quantity is 20 items or more.</li>\r\n	<li>Volume discount is applicable on the selling price of a product that is purchased in bulk.</li>\r\n	<li>If the product has a special price offer running, the volume discount will still be applied on the product when it is purchased in bulk.&nbsp;</li>  \r\n</ul>    '),(33,'RELATED_PRODUCTS',-1,'Similar Products','Link products with other similar products and manage their list here.','There is no limit to the number of similar products you can link. However, it is advised to link a sensible number of products together. ','The linked products are displayed under Similar Products on the product details page at the front end. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Linking all the similar products together is one way of helping buyers choose what they are looking for faster and buy more products that what they decided initially. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>When you link products together marking them as similar products, they are displayed under Similar Products on the product details page at the front end.&nbsp;</div></li>\r\n	<li>Buyers can click the products under the Similar Products section to visit their respective product details page and add them to their cart directly.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Link a sensible number of products to the main product since adding many products will not be user friendly. You might end up losing customers rather than gaining more sales.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>'),(34,'BUY_TOGETHER_PRODUCTS',-1,'Frequently Bought Together','Link products that are frequently bought together and manage the list here. ','It is advised to link only two or three products together at maximum.','Frequently bought together products are also known as add-on products. ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Frequently bought together products are also commonly known as add-on products. </li>\r\n	<li>These are the products that complement each other and can be suggested to buyers when they wish to buy any one of such products. </li>\r\n	<li>These products are listed with the main product on its product detail page under \'Buy Together Items\'. </li>\r\n	<li>The additional products are automatically selected and if the buyer doesn’t deselect them, they will be added to the cart along with the main product.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Since the products are considered as add-ons and are automatically selected, it is advised to link just 2 or 3 products with the main product. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>If you link many products together, it can cause you to lose your customers as not everyone will want to buy all the products.&nbsp;</div></li>\r\n</ul>      '),(35,'PROMOTIONS',-1,'PPC Promotions Management','Manage the list of PPC (pay-per-click) promotions (ads) configured by sellers and advertisers of the platform. ','Each promotion added needs to be approved by you (admin) before it can go live.','Define the PPC promotions cost and other details under Settings > System Configurations > PPC Management.','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Pay-per-click (PPC) is an advertising revenue model that is used by Advertisers to run ads on a platform. It is called PPC because when a target visitor clicks on the promotion, the person who started the promotion pays for the click. In short, advertisers pay the platform they are promoting their items on based on the clicks they receive. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Yo!Kart offers their advertisers the same features where they can set up PPC campaigns very easily on the platform. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Different types of campaigns can be created depending on if the advertiser is a seller as well or not on the platform. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>If the user is just an advertiser, the person can only create banner and slides campaigns, through which they can promote anything from inside the website or anything from outside the platform as well. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>On the other hand, if the user is both a seller and an advertiser, the person can promote their own shop, their own products, and also create banners and slides campaigns for both internal and external links.&nbsp;</div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Sellers can only create the promotions through their advertiser account, which is automatically created when they become a seller. And both the sellers and advertisers have to have a minimum balance in their wallet to run promotions on the platform. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Being the admin, you get to define the CPC (cost-per-click), rules and minimum balance needed for PPC promotions to run on the platform.&nbsp;</div></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>Manage all the PPC settings and define the costs under Settings > System Configurations > PPC Management.</div>     '),(36,'REWARDS_ON_PURCHASE',-1,'Reward on Purchase','Create reward plans for buyers based on the amount they spend on the platform. ','Define how many reward points equals to 1 {default currency} under Settings > System Configurations > Rewards Points.','Reward points will be credited to the buyer\'s account when their order amount will be equal or more than the defined purchase amount of a reward plan. ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Define how many reward points equals to 1 {default currency} under Settings > System Configurations > Rewards Points.</li>\r\n	<li>All the reward points related settings can be managed under Settings > System Configurations > Rewards Points. Or simply click the settings icon beside New to go to this settings page directly.&nbsp;</li>  \r\n	<li>Buyers can utilize these Rewards points during checkout.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">NOTE:</span>&nbsp;<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-c0e633c7-7fff-1c29-d6c1-c8d18cc73a9c\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"></span></span>Remember to turn ON&nbsp; the <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Activate to offer reward points on every purchase</span> toggle switch under the settings for your reward plans to work.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>         '),(37,'MANAGE_WEIGHTAGES',-1,'Product Event Weightages','Manage product event weightages the system uses to create a list of recommended products.','This submodule works only for those products that have product tags linked to them. ','The list of recommended products decided by this submodule is listed under the Recommended Product Tag Weightages module. ','','\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<div>Weightage means giving emphasis or priority to something.</div>\r\n		<div><br />\r\n			</div>\r\n		<div>Yo!Kart’s features include assisting buyers in making their purchase decisions faster by offering them recommendations and suggestions about what to purchase. The system is able to offer recommendations after it tracks every user’s actions on the platform.</div>\r\n		<div><br />\r\n			</div>\r\n		<div>How does it work? Different weightages are given to each action taken on the platform. Based on the weightages of an action, the platform understands a customer’s behavior, and uses this to display the right promotion to the right audience.&nbsp;</div>\r\n		<div><br />\r\n			</div>\r\n		<div>Although most of the process is handled automatically by the system, you can manage the weightages of the actions that help the process.&nbsp;</div></div>\r\n	<div><br />\r\n		</div></div>\r\n<div>Currently, the system has 3 events and you can only edit the weightage points for each. They include:</div>\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Products View:</span> When the product’s details are being viewed by a buyer on the respective product’s detail page.</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Time Spent on a Product (products time_spent): </span>When the buyer has spent a definite amount of time on the product detail page and views the complete page, by scrolling down to see the rest of the page details. </li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Product is purchased (products order_paid):</span> When the buyer places an order for a product, and completes the payment for the same.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>Using these events, products are recommended to a user under the recommended section.&nbsp;</div></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Once the product criteria are fulfilled and the system auto-calculates the event weightages for each product tag, it is allocated to each product in the system. With this, the recommended products list is prepared.&nbsp;</div></li>\r\n	<li>A product’s event weightage is calculated by adding the total weightage points earned by the product\'s tag, based on the events.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>This list of recommended products and their weightages are all listed under the Recommended Product Tag Weightages submodule (next submodule) for you to manage.</div></div>        '),(38,'RECOMMENDED_TAG_PRODUCTS_WEIGHTAGES',-1,'Recommended Product Tag Weightages','Manage and customize the recommended list of products based on their product tag weightages. ','This feature will be functional only for those products that are linked to product tags.','This submodule is directly linked to the previous submodule - Promotions > Product Event Weightages. ','','\r\n<div>This submodule lists all the products, their product tags, and their system allocated weightages.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div>This list of recommended products is decided by the product event weightages as defined under Promotions > Product Event Weightages.&nbsp; </div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>These products are the ones displayed under the Recommended Product\'s section. However, the recommended product list can be customized accordingly.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>This list displays two weightage values:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">System Weightage:</span> This is the weightage points given to the respective product based on the weightage points obtained by its tags. This value is calculated with the helps of the weightages defined for different events listed under&nbsp;Promotions > Product Event Weightages.&nbsp;</li>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Custom Weightage:</span> You can customize the weightages for each product&nbsp;and tag associated with so that the respective product can be displayed higher or lower in the recommended product section.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<div>Once you customize the product weightage to edit the recommended product list, the products will be displayed based on the new weightage you added. </div>\r\n	<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>The customized weightage value has a validity as well. Define the validity in the field beside its value.&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>Once the validity end, the system weightage of the respective product will be reinstated and the recommended list will consider it then.<br />\r\n		</div><br />\r\n	</div>    '),(39,'MANAGE_DISCOUNT_COUPONS',-1,'Discount Coupons','Manage all the discount coupons created for both products (for buyers) and subscription packages (for sellers).','An expired coupon cannot be activated.','Bind a coupon to a specific product, category, user, shop, and/or brand by using the links icon. ','','\r\n<div>A discount coupon is a code that a buyer can redeem at checkout and get a discount on their order. This submodule allows you to manage all the coupons created on the platform. There are two types of discount coupons:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Product Purchase:</span> Used by the buyer when they purchase a product. This discount coupon type can be linked to a specific product, category, user, shop, and/or brand. If a coupon is linked to anything specific, it becomes applicable only for those things. For instance, if the coupon is linked to a shop, the buyer will be able to avail the coupon only for products sold under that shop. And if it is linked to a category or brand, products of the respective category or brand will be applicable for a discount. However, if the coupon is linked to a user, then only that user will be able to avail the coupon’s discount.</li>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Subscription Packages:</span> Used by the seller when purchasing a subscription plan to set up their shop on the platform. This discount coupon can be linked to a subscription package plan. If you like the discount coupon to a plan, it will be applicable only for that plan.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>Whenever a user applies a discount coupon during checkout, the coupon gets locked in the system for a period of 15 minutes so that user can proceed with payment and after that coupons are deemed used.&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div><br />\r\n		</div>\r\n	<div>All the active coupons are listed at the front end under the discount coupon list.</div>&nbsp;</div>    '),(40,'MANAGE_BADGES',-1,'Badges ','Add and manage custom badges that can be linked to products (displayed on product detail page) and shops (displayed on the shop detail page).','The linking of a badge to the shop, product or product variant can be done by both the seller and you (admin). ','','','\r\n<div>These badges are used to build trust among buyers that visit the platform. Some examples of badges include, Authentic, Verified, Premium, Best Price, and so on.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n	</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;\"></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;\"></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Points to Note:</span></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All the badges you create will be visible to the sellers under Seller > Promotions > Badges on their dashboard. They can request to link a badge to their shop or product accordingly. These requests can be managed under Requests > Badge Requests.</li>\r\n	<li>Based upon the source of generation (trigger type), badges are classified into 2 types, namely Manual and Automatic.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>Each has been explained below in details:</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n	</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;\">1. Manual Badges</span></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>There are two kinds of Manual badges - open and closed.</li>\r\n	<li>Open manual badges can be assigned directly to a shop, product or product variant by the seller.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Close manual badges require the approval of the admin (you) before the seller can link them to their shop, product or product variant.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>When assigning a manual badge, defining the time period for the badge is not mandatory. However, the badge has to be linked to a product, a product variant or the shop (depending on the badge type).</li>\r\n	<li>The linking of a badge to the shop, product or product variant can be done by both the seller and you (admin).&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;\">2. Automatic Badges</span></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>These badges will be allotted to a shop or seller automatically once the shop or seller fulfills some predefined conditions that you (admin) define for the respective badge when creating it.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>These badges cannot be assigned manually and do not require any approval.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><br />\r\n	</div> '),(41,'MANAGE_RIBBONS',-1,'Ribbons','Add and manage ribbons by customizing the ribbon name, its color, and link it to a shop, product, or product variant.','Only you can create a list of all the ribbons that will be used on the platform.','Ribbon always appear on the top right corner of the product image.','','\r\n<div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n	</ul></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;Features:</div>\r\n<ul>    \r\n	<li>You are the only one who has the authority to create Ribbons.</li>\r\n	<li>All the Ribbons added by you will be visible to all the Sellers.</li>    \r\n	<li>Ribbon will be available to all the Sellers for an indefinite period of time unless you delete or deactivate a specific Ribbon.</li>    \r\n	<li>The display of these Ribbons at the Front end will depend on which kind of record it has been linked to.&nbsp;</li>    \r\n	<li>Ribbons can be linked/attached at Product variant or Seller Product or Shop level.</li>    \r\n	<li>Ribbons will not be displayed on the product image thumbnails (small sized images).</li>\r\n</ul> '),(42,'SELLER_SUBSCRIPTION_PACKAGES',-1,'Seller Subscription Packages','Manage various paid and free subscription packages for onboarding sellers onto the platform.','Once the subscription package type (free or paid) has been selected and saved, it cannot be changed. ','Commission set for a package will act as default commission for the seller who has subscribed to that package.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Click on New to create a new package. Add multiple different conditions to the package including the commission rate, products allowed, inventory allowed, and the number of images a seller can add per catalog. </li> \r\n	<li>Click on the Settings icon to view and add duration plans under the package. </li>\r\n	<li>Once a package is created, you cannot delete it. You can only edit it. If you do not want to use the package, deactivate it by turning off the status toggle switch under the status column beside it. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(43,'AFFILIATE_COMMISSIONS',-1,'Affiliate Commissions ','Set commission rates for affiliate users including the category level, and/or the affiliate level.','','By default, there is one affiliate rate that is applicable for all the affiliates that join the platform. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This default affiliate commission rate cannot be deleted. You can edit this rate by clicking on the edit icon beside it. </li>\r\n	<li>Customize various commission rates specific to each affiliate and/or specific to a product category. You can create commission rate settings where an affiliate gets a specific amount of commission if they sell a product under a specific category. </li>\r\n	<li>Set a commission rate for a specific category on the platform. Under this, if an affiliate makes a sale of a product under the defined category, they will be rewarded with the commission as defined under the rule. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(44,'MANAGE_ABUSIVE_KEYWORDS',-1,'Restricted Keywords (Abusive)','Protect your storefront from all kinds of spam and abusive comments by creating a directory of restricted words.','','Users will be restricted from using words listed in this list when posting reviews for purchased products on the platform. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Add spam and abusive words and phrases in every language to this list using the New button. There is no definition for the kind of words you consider spam.</li> \r\n	<li>Edit an entry by clicking on the Edit icon beside it. </li>\r\n	<li>Delete the entry by clicking on the delete icon beside it. </li>\r\n	<li>All the words listed under this module will be blocked by the system when a user tries to post the same while leaving a review anywhere on the platform.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(45,'EMPTY_CART_ITEMS',-1,'Empty Cart Links','Manage the title message and link that will be displayed on the message notifying a buyer about their empty cart. ','','Redirect your users to popular pages like All Categories, All Products, Top Brands, and more as per your business model.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Create a list of empty cart messages that will be displayed to users who have an empty cart. </li>\r\n	<li>Enter a title message and a URL that will be linked to it. The title will be hyperlinked with the URL.</li>\r\n	<li>The hyperlinked message title will be displayed along with a message to the buyer on the front end if they have an empty cart.</li>\r\n	<li>When a buyer clicks on the hyperlinked title message, they will be redirected to the hyperlinked page. </li>\r\n	<li>Edit an entry by clicking on the edit icon, and delete an entry by clicking on the delete icon. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(46,'FAKE_SHOP_REPORT_REASONS',-1,'Report Shop Reasons','Manage list of concerns raised by buyers while they report seller’s shop as spam.','','Admin users can keep track of shops that have been reported as spam from Product management > Shops Listing > Reports header.','','\r\n'),(47,'BLOG_CATEGORIES',-1,'Blog Categories','Manage blog categories to sort and organise content into different sections.','','','','Deleting a category does not delete the posts in that category. Instead posts that were only assigned to the deleted category are set to the category&nbsp;\r\n '),(48,'BLOG_POSTS',-1,'Blog Posts','Create and manage every blog post (article) that will be posted on the blog page of the platform. ','Mark the blog as published (using the toggle switch beside it) for the post to be displayed at the front end. ','Link a single blog to multiple different blog post categories.','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>A blog is a web page that holds information related to the theme of the website. This information is updated on a regular basis. A blog page is normally made up of posts, also known as articles that share the information. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Create and manage the blog posts (articles) that will be posted on the website’s blog, under this module.&nbsp;</div>\r\n		<div><br />\r\n			</div></li>\r\n	<li>Define how your blog page will look by categorizing the blogs accordingly and managing all its settings under this page.</li>\r\n	<div><br />\r\n		</div>\r\n	<li>Blog posts that are marked as featured, will be displayed under the Featured blogs heading on the blog page at the front end. </li>\r\n	<li>Activate or deactivate the comment section for each blog post when creating it.</li>\r\n</ul> '),(49,'BLOG_CONTRIBUTION',-1,'Blog Contribution Requests','Manage the all the blog post requests placed by users, in case they want to share their thoughts and opinion.','If you accept a blog contribution request, it won\'t be posted as a blog automatically. ','You will have to create a blog post and publish the same, referring to the blog contribution data shared by the user. ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Visitors and users can share their blog post ideas (blog contributions) with you by clicking the Contribute button on any blog post page. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>This button is located under the Popular and Featured blog posts section on the right side of the page.&nbsp;</div></li>\r\n	<li>When a user clicks this button, they are directed to the blog contribution page. They need to fill this form and click Submit for sending the blog contribution request to you.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Every contribution request made using this process will be listed under this submodule.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>The status of the \"Contribution Request\" by default will be \"Pending\".</li>  \r\n	<li>Edit the blog contribution status as per your action:    \r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Approved: If you like the content and consider it appropriate to be published.</li>    \r\n			<li>Posted: If you create a blog post with the content and publish it at the front end.&nbsp;</li>    \r\n      \r\n			<li>Rejected: If you find the submitted content inappropriate and don\'t want to publish it.</li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n</ul> '),(50,'BLOG_COMMENTS',-1,'Blog Comments','Manage the comments posted by users on the blog posts.','No comment is posted directly without your approval. ','You can edit the comment as well as the publish status. ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>While creating a blog post, you have the option to activate or deactivate the comments section, allowing or restricting users from commenting on the respective blog post. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>For the blog posts where you allow users to comment, a comment section is visible below the respective blog posts. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>However, a user can leave a comment only if they have an account on the platform and have logged into their account. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>If they are not logged in, a message is displayed saying, \"Login required to post a comment.</div></li>\r\n	<li>The user needs to click the \"Login” link and log into their account. Once done, they will see the comment section and can leave a comment accordingly.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>No comment is directly posted on the website. You need to approve the comment before it is published. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>All these comments are listed under this submodule for you to review accordingly.&nbsp;</div>\r\n		<div><br />\r\n			</div></li>\r\n	<li>By default Status of the \"Comments\" posted will be marked \"Pending\".</li>  \r\n	<li>Take the following actions on each posted comments:\r\n    \r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Approved: If you approve the comment and consider it appropriate to be published.</li>    \r\n      \r\n			<li>Rejected: If you find the submitted comment inappropriate and don\'t want it to get published at the front end.</li>\r\n			<li>Pending: If you have not yet made a decision on the comment.&nbsp;</li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n</ul> '),(51,'REPORT_SALES_OVERTIME',-1,'Sales Over Time Report','Detailed sales trend report that includes information on the gross sale, total ordered quantity, and more for a respective date.','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Specify dates and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n	<li>Click on a date to view the sales made on that particular date. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(52,'REPORT_PRODUCTS',-1,'Product Catalog Sales Report','Detailed information on product-specific sales data. ','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Specify dates and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>  '),(53,'REPORT_PRODUCT_VARIANTS',-1,'Product Variant Sales Report','Detailed product variant sales report that includes information on sold quantity, gross sale, refund amount, and more for each variant.','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Apply filters from the advance search and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>    '),(54,'REPORT_SHOPS',-1,'Shop\'s Spam Reports','View the list of Spam Reports made against the Shop, and take action accordingly.','Each Spam Report displays the report reason, an additional message, reporting person, and time the shop was reported. ','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>View all the spam reports made against the respective Shop.</li>\r\n	<li>Find out who reported the shop as a spam and the reason to report the same.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>No actions can be taken for these Spam Reports. You can only view them.</li>\r\n	<li>These spam reports are not visible on the front end. </li>\r\n	<li>The Shop is affected by this reporting only if you take an action against the said shop due to the report made.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>    '),(55,'REPORT_CUSTOMERS',-1,'Customer Sales Report','Detailed report on each customer\'s purchase behavior that includes information on the number of orders placed, total amount spent, and more.  ','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Specify name/email and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(56,'USERS_REPORT',-1,'Buyers','Detailed buyers\' report that includes information on item purchased, rewards earned by each user. ','','','',''),(57,'SELLERS_REPORT',-1,'Sellers Report','Detailed seller report that includes information on the number of orders received, earnings and ratings of each seller.','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Apply filters from advance search and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(58,'AFFILIATES_REPORT',-1,'Affiliates Report','Detailed affiliate report that includes information on the number of registrations made, total revenue earned, and more. ','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Specify dates and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>  '),(59,'ADVERTISERS_REPORT',-1,'Advertisers Report','Detailed advertiser report that includes information on their registration date, total and active promotions they have, and more.  ','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Apply filters from advance search and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(60,'REPORT_EARNINGS',-1,'Earnings Report','Detailed earnings report that includes information on revenue generated through subscription, advertisement and sales.','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Specify dates and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(61,'REPORT_PROFIT_BY_PRODUCTS',-1,'Profit By Products Report','Detailed report on product sales specifc admin earnings.','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Specify dates and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(62,'REPORT_PREFERRED_PAYMENT_METHOD',-1,'Preferred Payment Method','Detailed report of the preferred payment method used by users.','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Apply filters from advance search and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(63,'REPORT_PAYOUT',-1,'Payout Report','Detailed report of the payout transactions for reward discounts, affiliate commissions, and coupon discounts.','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Specify dates and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(64,'REPORT_TRANSACTION',-1,'Wallet Transactions','Detailed user-specific wallet transactions report.','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Apply filters from advance search and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(65,'REPORT_SUBSCRIPTION_BY_PLAN',-1,'Subscription Report by Plan','Detailed report of subscription plans available, number of times each plan was bought, active subscribers of each plan, and more. ','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(66,'REPORT_SUBSCRIPTION_BY_SELLER',-1,'Subscription Report by Seller','Detailed seller-specific subscription package report.','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(67,'THRESHOLD_PRODUCTS',-1,'Threshold Products','View the sellers\' product inventories whose stock level (unit level) is equal to or less than the defined threshold limit.','The system doesn\'t keep track of whether an alert about the stock was sent to the seller or not. ','Send a reminder (email notification) to the respective seller using the Email to Seller icon regarding the declining stock levels. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sellers are allowed to setup threshold limits while adding the product inventory details.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>You (admin) can manage the threshold limits under Product Management > Seller\'s Product Inventory.</li>\r\n	<li>For products that have a threshold limit, when it reaches the limit, it will be added to this list.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>To alert the seller about the declining stock, click on the Email to Seller icon to notify them accordingly.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Manage the alert email’s content under Settings > Email Templates > Threshold Level Notification - Seller option.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>   '),(68,'RATING_TYPES',-1,'Rating Types','Manage available rating types for buyers to submit store reviews.','Default \'Product\' rating type cannot be deactivated.','Product, Shop & Delivery are default rating types. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Click on the Add New button to add a new rating type.</li>\r\n	<li>Rating types show on the product detail page under customer reviews to buyers.</li>\r\n	<li>The newly added product types cannot be deleted. They can only be deactivated using the toggle button.</li>\r\n	<li>Whenever required, only \'shop\' and \'delivery\' types can be deactivated. </li>\r\n	<li>For the rating types to appear on the product detail page, it needs to bind with the product category from Product Management > Categories > Category Setup Form > Rating Types.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(69,'MANAGE_ORDER_RETURN_REQUESTS',-1,'Order Return Requests','Manage all the order return requested by buyers on the platform. ','','Both you and the seller can edit the order return request status.','','\r\n<div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Add and view the comments for the order return request placed by buyers.&nbsp;</li>\r\n		<li>Update the order return request status for any order.&nbsp;</li>\r\n		<li>Keep track of every order return requested through this module.&nbsp;</li>\r\n		<li>You have the option to send a message on the communication thread, while the seller is already communicating with the buyer.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul></div>        '),(70,'SHIPPING_COMPANY_USERS',-1,'Shipping Company Users','Set up the information of each delivery agent that you will be using for the shipping process.','These are important for both the manual shipping process or when a shipping service plugin is activated. ','You or the seller cannot move ahead and mark an order as shipped without selecting a shipping company user.','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Add shipping company or their delivery team members under this section.</li>  \r\n	<li>Bind the shipping users corresponding to the orders that are being delivered by admin. This is done under Orders > Orders, when you are about to change the order status.&nbsp;</li>  \r\n	<li>In case of a COD order, the amount received by the shipping company users and debited from his/her accounts.</li>  \r\n	<li>In the case of the COD order marked as completed the amount is credited to the user account by assuming that the admin collected the COD order amount for the assigned order.</li>  \r\n	<li>Admin can manually Credit/Debit transactions into the shipping users\' account.</li>\r\n</ul> '),(71,'MANAGE_URL_REWRITING',-1,'URL Rewriting','Create SEO-friendly URLs for web pages to make it easier for users to remember and search engines to crawl.','Each web page URL should be unique. No two URLs can be the same. ','An SEO-friendly URL should be short, clear and should include the main keyword that describes the page.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Only last part of the URL, called the slug, can be edited. </li>\r\n	<li>Most of the URL entries in this list were created when the respective page was created. For instance, when you create a brand and create an SEO-friendly URL for it on the same form, it is added to this list.</li>\r\n	<li>Click on the delete icon to delete a URL. It will delete the SEO-friendly URL that you created for the respective page. You can still visit the page, but the URL of this page will be a system-generated one. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(72,'MANAGE_IMAGE_ATTRIBUTES',-1,'Image Attributes','Create image attributes for all the images uploaded to the platform for the search engines to crawl.','Alt tag is an HTML attribute applied to image tags to provide a text alternative for search engines.','An alt tag is also known as alt attribute and alt description. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>There are two attributes for each image - image title and image alt tag. Both of these image attributes can be the same. </li>\r\n	<li>You can use the same keyword or name for multiple image attributes.</li>\r\n	<li>Notes about ALT Tag and how they help in SEO:\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Image ALT tags are helpful for accessibility reasons. </li>\r\n			<li>It helps participants with physical or vision impairments. </li>\r\n			<li>The image attributes help the image show up in the search image results.</li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n</ul> '),(73,'MANAGE_CONTENT_PAGES',-1,'Content Pages','Create, manage, and modify the website’s pages and their content without the need for specialized technical knowledge.','Try both webpage layouts before finalizing and publishing the website page.','By default, three main pages including the About Us, Privacy Policy, and Terms and Conditions page will already be in the list. ','','\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>Create, manage, and modify the website’s pages and their content without the need for specialized technical knowledge.</div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>By default, three main pages including the About Us page, Privacy Policy Page and Terms and Conditions page will already be in the list once you purchase the product.</li>\r\n		<li>You can easily edit these page content details and even create more pages for the website by clicking New.</li>\r\n		<li>The process to create a new content page for the platform includes, giving it a name, choosing a layout, and uploading the content and media that will be displayed on the page under the language data tab.</li>\r\n		<li>The system offers two types of layouts. To view the layout designs available, click Layouts.</li>\r\n	</ul></div>  '),(74,'MANAGE_CONTENT_BLOCK',-1,'Content Blocks','View and update the content in various pages of the platform using this predefined list of content blocks.\r\n','Once a content block is updated, the updated content will be displayed everywhere the content block is used.','Deactivating a content block will remove it from the front end. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The platform allows you to personalize multiple sections of the website by editing its content and images through these content blocks</li> \r\n	<li>The system comes with 14 pre-defined content blocks that you can personalize</li>\r\n	<li>You can\'t add nor delete a content block. If you do not want to publish a listed content block, deactivate it by turning OFF the toggle switch beside it</li>\r\n	<li>Edit the content block details by clicking on the edit icon beside it. Almost every content block has a different layout. Update them accordingly.</li>\r\n</ul>  '),(75,'MANAGE_FAQ_CATEGORIES',-1,'FAQ Categories','Organize the FAQ content that comes on the FAQs page by categorizing them into group via this page. ','This page only allows you to create and manage FAQ Categories. ','To add FAQs under an FAQ Category, click the FAQ Listing icon beside the respective category. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you do not want to publish an FAQ category, deactivate it by turning OFF the toggle switch beside it.</li> \r\n	<li>Click the FAQ Listing icon to view the list of all the FAQs added under a category. Add more FAQs under this category by clicking on New. </li>\r\n	<li>When adding a new FAQ data, enter the question as the FAQ title and the answer to this question in the description field. </li>\r\n	<li>When you delete an FAQ category, all the FAQs under it will also get deleted from the system. </li>\r\n</ul>   '),(76,'MANAGE_FAQ',-1,'FAQs','Create and manage all the FAQs that will be displayed under the respective FAQs category. ','','','','\r\n'),(77,'MANAGE_TESTIMONIAL',-1,'Testimonials','View, edit or delete the existing testimonials left by users.','No user is allowed to directly post a testimonial.','Only you can add using the New button, and edit a testimonial using the edit icon. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Let the audience know more about your service by sharing all the testimonials you received from your users. </li>\r\n	<li>The testimonials added here will be reflected on the home page at the front end when the testimonial collection is active. </li>\r\n	<li>Only you can add and edit a testimonial. No user is allowed to directly post a testimonial.</li>\r\n	<li>If a user wants to leave a review about the platform, they can share their review with you via email or so. </li>\r\n	<li>To display this testimonial on the platform, you will have to add it under this module by clicking on the New button. </li>\r\n	<li>Unpublish a testimonial by turning OFF the toggle switch beside it. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(78,'MANAGE_TAX_STRUCTURE',-1,'Tax Structure','Define and manage all the tax structures that will be linked to each tax category rule.','Give the tax structure correct names as they will be displayed at the front end, during the checkout. ','A tax structure can be single-tiered or multi-tiered, based on the government levels levying the respective tax. ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n  \r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>A tax structure can be single-tiered or multi-tiered based on the government levels levying the respective tax. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Government levels can refer to different governments within a country such as the federal, state, local, district, and union territory governments, or different government agencies within a country. It can also refer to the governments of different countries. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Some countries only have a single-tier sales tax structure. This means that the sales tax will be paid only to one government level. On the other hand, some countries have a multi-tier sales tax structure, where two or more government levels levy the sales tax.&nbsp;</div></li> \r\n  \r\n</ul>\r\n<div>The two types of tax structures:</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Single Tax Structure:</span> In this structure, the tax is imposed by only one level of government. A common instance of such a structure is VAT (Value added tax) and the US sales tax. \r\nVAT is a single-tiered tax structure used in Germany. The US sales tax is also a single-tiered tax structure.</li>\r\n</ul>A single tax structure doesn\'t have tax components, while a combined tax structure has tax components. For example, if the tax name is \'GST\', you need to add three components: CGST, SGST, and IGST.<br />\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Combined Tax Structure (multi-tiered):</span> In this structure, the total tax is a combination of taxes levied at multiple government levels. \r\nAn example to help you understand this is the GST (Goods &amp; Services Tax) in India. This tax is made up of 4 government levels: Central GST (CGST), State GST (SGST), Union Territory Goods and Services Tax (UTGST), and Integrated GST (IGST). Hence, GST is a combined tax structure.</li>  \r\n</ul>'),(79,'MANAGE_TAX_CATEGORIES',-1,'Tax Categories','Manage all the tax categories of the platform that will be used to link to products to determine their final tax charges. ','If a Tax Services plugin has been activated from Settings > Plugins > Tax Services, the manually added tax categories will not work. And this list will display all the plugin\'s tax categories.','Each tax category can have multiple tax rules, which can be defined using the tax category rules icon.','','A tax category is a list of rules for a set type of products. There are two points to note:<br />\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Each government level levies a different tax rate for the same product.</li>\r\n	<li>Each type of product has a different sales tax. For instance, electronic items have a different sales tax rate as compared to clothing items, and so on.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>To ensure that all the tax rates and rules are added correctly, you need to create a tax category for each type of product. For instance, create tax categories for mobile phones, baby clothes, and so on. Give the tax category the same name as the product category to make things simpler. Once done, you can then add the tax rules of the tax categories.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you configure and activate a Sales Tax Services plugin, this page will synchronize with the plugin and all the plugin’s tax categories will be listed here (along with the tax categories you created). You can view the plugin’s tax categories, identify the categories for each product, and link them accordingly.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>In this situation, let us assume that you bind a product to a manually-created tax category (which is possible and they will bind). This product will not be displayed at the front end. Only those products that are linked to the plugin’s tax categories will be displayed at the front end. Refer to Tax for more information.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>If you are following the manual tax management process, ensure that the sales tax service plugin has been deactivated (even if it has not been configured). This is mainly because, with an activated plugin, you will not be able to view the tax structure and the tax categories rules submodules (that help to add the tax rules that will guide the whole tax process). So, check it before moving ahead.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Other points to note:</span></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hide the \'Tax Code\' input field from the form by editing its settings under Settings > System Configuration > Product tab. This field is only helpful when you are using a third-party Tax services under Settings > Plugins > Tax Service Plugin.</li> \r\n  \r\n	<li>Make sure you \'Sync\' the Tax categories under Settings > Plugins > Tax Service Plugin, when the Tax service plugin is enabled.</li>\r\n	<li>Tax applied varies with the Product categories and across different States. \r\nTherefore, you need to first create Tax Categories based on the nature of the Products the Tax rules will be applied and then create the rules for them.</li>\r\n</ul>  '),(80,'MANAGE_TAX_CATEGORIES_RULE',-1,'Tax Category\'s Rules','Manage all the Country/State specific tax rules for each Tax Category.','Tax Rules can only be configured under the Tax Category module through the Tax Category Rules icon.','This submodule only helps you manage all the tax category rules (regardless of the tax category they fall under) you created.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The tax structures, tax categories, and tax category rules are all created via the last two submodules. </li>\r\n	<li>This submodule only helps you manage the tax category rules you created. </li>\r\n	<li>It lists all the rules together regardless of which tax category the rule belongs to. </li>\r\n	<li>You can edit the rule or delete it. However, you cannot add a new tax rule.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>If you want to add a new tax category rule, you will need to do it via Tax > Tax Categories > Tax Category Rules icon.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(82,'MANAGE_PRODUCT_REVIEWS',-1,'Product Reviews','Manage the reviews posted by buyers for the delivered items.','Buyers can only post reviews, if the review module has been activated from Settings > System Configurations > Reviews tab.','Create different rating types to club with the review form under Settings > Rating Types.','','\r\n<div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Activate the review module under&nbsp; Settings > System Configurations > Reviews tab to allow buyers to share their feedback in text format for the purchased products, and their shopping experience, once their order process has been marked as completed.</li>\r\n		<li>You can combine the review process with a rating section as well. </li>\r\n		<li>Reviews are sentiments shared in a text format, while ratings are a star score from 1-5 stars. Combining the both help new customers make faster decisions when searching if a product is worth purchasing or not. </li>\r\n		<li>Create and manage the different rating types (that will be collected together with the review) under Settings > Rating Types. </li>\r\n		<li>These rating types will then be displayed to buyers along with the review form at the front end. </li>\r\n		<li>To block users from using abusive words, define the respective words under Settings > Abusive Keywords. </li>\r\n		<li>Once you define the list of abusive words, buyers who try to use any of these words while submitting a review, will be prompted with an error message and won’t be able to post the same unless these words are removed from the review. </li>\r\n		<li>Once an appropriate review and rating is shared by a buyer, it is added to this list where you can manage the same accordingly by approving it, rejecting it or leaving it with the pending status.</li>\r\n		<li>Approved reviews are posted at the front end.</li>\r\n		<li>To gain more control over which reviews are displayed at the front end, you can choose to manually publish reviews instead. </li>\r\n		<li>To deactivate the auto-publish settings, edit the default status of every review received as Pending, under Settings > System Configurations > Reviews tab. On the other hand, to allow reviews to be posted directly at the front end, update the default review status as Approved.</li>\r\n		<div>\r\n			<div><br />\r\n				</div><br />\r\n			</div>\r\n		<div><br />\r\n			</div>\r\n		<div><br />\r\n			</div>\r\n	</ul></div>   '),(88,'MANAGE_PRODUCTS',-1,'Product Catalog','Manage the catalog of the platform, listing all the products added by you (admin) and the sellers. ','This catalog includes both the master products and seller\'s products.','Master catalog includes products for everyone on the platform. Seller catalog includes products for the respective seller only. ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>There are two types of catalogs on the platform - master catalog and seller catalog.</li>\r\n	<li>The master catalog holds all the master products. Sellers can add inventories to these products and sell the same in their shop.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>A seller catalog holds all the respective seller\'s products. Only the respective seller can inventories to their products and sell it in their shop. It is not available for any other seller. (NOTE: You can restrict sellers from creating their own catalog under Settings > System Configurations > Product tab).</li>\r\n	<li>You can differentiate between a master product and a seller product through the value under the User column. If the user is \"admin,\" it is a master product. If the user is a seller\'s name, the product belongs to that seller\'s catalog.&nbsp;</li>  \r\n	<li>A product is displayed at the front end (store front) only when a seller adds its inventory details.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>         '),(89,'ADD_PRODUCT',-1,'Add Product','Create or Edit all the products (Admin/Sellers) available on the platform.','','','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Admin\'s products will be available to all the sellers to add to their inventory </li>  \r\n	<li>Seller products, added by a specific seller will be available only to him to add to his inventory. No other sellers can add that product to their inventory.</li>  \r\n	<li>Any product will be displayed on the front end only when a seller has added an inventory for that product.</li>  \r\n	<li>Sellers can add inventories as per the settings \'Allow Sellers To Add Products\' enabled from Settings > System Configuration > Product</li>\r\n</ul> '),(90,'CUSTOM_PRODUCT_REQUEST',-1,'Master Product Requests','Manage the status of new master products requested by sellers.','Approved products will be available for all sellers to sell in their shop after they add the respective product\'s inventory details. ','','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>A master product is requested by sellers when the respective product is not a part of the master catalog, and they would like to add the same to it.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Once the request is approved by you (admin), the product becomes a part of the master catalog. This product then becomes available for all the sellers, for which they can add inventory details and sell in their shop accordingly.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Allow or disallow sellers from requesting to add a master product to the master catalog under Settings > System Configuration > Product Tab.<br />\r\n		</li>\r\n</ul>      '),(91,'SELLER_APPROVAL_REQUESTS',-1,'Seller Registration Requests','Manage the status of new sellers that have registered with the platform.','This module is applicable only if a seller requires the admin\'s approval to join the platform. ','Define the seller approval settings under Settings > System Configurations > User Account tab.','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Activate/deactivate the seller approval feature under Settings > System Configuration > User Account Tab.</li>\r\n	<li>Deactivating the feature will allow sellers to directly join the platform and set up their shop without your approval.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>If you deactivate the feature, this module will still be visible. Moreover, any requests every places when the feature was active will also be visible in this list.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>          '),(92,'ORDER_CANCELLATION_REQUESTS',-1,'Order Cancellation Requests','Manage all the order cancellation requests placed by the buyers. ','Only you can decline or approve a cancellation request. Sellers can just view the request, but cannot take any action on it. ','Update the order cancellation reasons that buyers can have under Orders > Order Cancellation Reasons.','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Approve or decline all the order cancellation requests that are made.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>When a cancellation request is made, the request is sent to you and to the respective seller.</li>\r\n	<li>Only you (admin) can approve or decline an order cancellation request. The seller can just view the request and its updated, but cannot take any action regarding the same.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Only you (admin) have the option to view all the comments made once the cancellation request has been approved or cancelled.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Update the order cancellation reasons that buyers can have under Orders > Order Cancellation Reasons.</li>\r\n</ul>        '),(93,'MANAGE_ORDERS',-1,'Orders ','View and manage every order placed by buyers on the platform.','Orders with \"PAID\" payment status cannot be deleted.','Newly placed orders always get listed at the top.','','\r\n<div>Things you can manage and do under this module:</div>\r\n<ul>   \r\n	<li>Manage the order\'s status and view their status history.</li>  \r\n   \r\n	<li>You have the option to notify Buyers of the orders status update.</li>\r\n	<li>Add the transaction status for the orders.</li>   \r\n	<li>Print invoices for the orders.</li>\r\n	<li>Action buttons on this page facilitate you to view order details/delete that particular order.&nbsp;</li>  \r\n	<li>Order Status can be managed under left navigation > Orders > Order Statuses</li>  \r\n	<li>Orders configuration related settings can be managed under Settings > System Configurations > Checkout tab.</li>\r\n</ul>  '),(94,'MANAGE_ABANDONED_CART',-1,'Abandoned Cart','Generate discount coupons for the Abandoned items listed below and attract the buyers to complete the purchase.','Abandoned items listed here will be removed from the list after 3 months.','','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Filter the list based on the products removed from the cart, products left in the card and products recovered after being removed from the cart, using the search functionality at the top of the page.</li>\r\n	<li>Generate discount coupons and share them with buyers for the Abandoned cart item.</li>\r\n	<li>When you create a discount coupon for the product abandoned, the system will share up to 2 email notifications for the same with the respective buyer.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Abandoned items listed here will be removed from the list after 3 months. Along with this, the respective buyer\'s cart will also be emptied (if the products were left in the cart for more than 3 months).</li>\r\n</ul>  '),(95,'MANAGE_SLIDES',-1,'Homepage Slides','Manage all the slides that will be displayed in a slider at the top of the website\'s home page.','Multiple slides can be added here, but only four at a time will be displayed on the frontend.','Promotional slides added by advertisers and sellers will also be displayed along with these home page slides.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The slides that you add under this module will all be displayed at the top of the home page.</li> \r\n  \r\n	<li>Admin can attach a link with each slide.</li>  \r\n	<li>Users of the Storefront will be directed to the attached link once they click these slides.</li>\r\n	<li>You can add multiple home page sliders by clicking on the New button.</li> \r\n	<li>The system will randomly choose 4 slides to display every time.</li> \r\n	<li>If there are many promotional slides in the queue, they will be given a higher priority and will be displayed most of the time instead of these home slides.</li> \r\n	<li>Hyperlink the slide to a specific URL when adding the slide details. With this, when a buyer clicks on the slide, they will be directed to the hyperlinked page.</li>\r\n</ul> '),(96,'MANAGE_BANNER_LOCATIONS',-1,'Banner Locations','Manage all the banner locations on the platform, and their list of banners.','Only one banner location is added in this list. To add another banner location, contact the support team.','Only advertisers and you (admin) can add a promotional banner on the platform.','','\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>Banners are used for promoting various things on the platform. Yo!Kart allows both advertisers and you to promote banners at the front end.</div>\r\n	<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>There are two places on the platform where you can manage where the front end banner location, including:</div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>CMS > Collections: Under this submodule, you get to create banner collections for the homepage. You can create multiple banner collections for the homepage only and through this module.&nbsp;</li>\r\n		<li>CMS > Banners: All the other banner locations (other than the homepage collections) are listed under this submodule.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<div>There are two kinds of banners in the system:</div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Promotional Banners:</span> These are banners added as a promotion material by advertisers. While creating a promotional banner, advertisers have an option to choose where the banner will be displayed. The list of options include the homepage collection section(s) and the locations listed under this module. All the promotional banners added by an advertiser are listed under Promotions > PPC Promotions Management.</li>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Banners:</span> Banners added by you in the system. These can be any kind of banners as you are in charge of them.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<div>Excluding the banners added under any homepage collections, all the other banners (regardless if promotional or not), will be listed under the respective banner locations’ list of banners.</div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>So, if a promotional banner is added by an advertiser and its location is set as the product detail page banner, this banner’s details will be visible in both the PPC Promotions Management list and the product detail page banner’s list (explained below).</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<div>With this clear, this submodule lists all the other banner locations on the platform (excluding the homepage banner collections). Banner locations basically mean the places where the banners will be displayed at the front end.</div></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>By default, there is only one banner location added in the system under this submodule, which is the product detail page banner location. </li>\r\n	<li>This implies that there is a banner section located at the bottom of every product detail page. It comes below the product review section on the product detail page.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>You cannot create a banner location under this submodule. If you want to add other locations for your banners, you will need to contact the Yo!Kart support team and have it integrated into the system at the code level. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>This submodule only allows you to manage this banner location details including the banner location title and promotion cost.&nbsp;</div></li>\r\n</ul>    '),(97,'MANAGE_BANNERS',-1,'Banners','Add and manage banners displayed on each product detail page.','At a time, only two banners will be displayed regardless of the number of active banners in this list. ','Both advertisers and you can add banners that will be displayed on the product detail page at the front end. ','','\r\n<div>Banners are used for promoting various things on the platform. Yo!Kart allows both advertisers and you to promote banners at the front end.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>There are two kinds of banners in the system:</div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Promotional Banners:</span> These are banners added as a promotion material by advertisers. While creating a promotional banner, advertisers have an option to choose where the banner will be displayed. The list of options include the homepage collection section(s) and the locations listed under this module. All the promotional banners added by an advertiser are listed under Promotions > PPC Promotions Management.</li>\r\n		<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Banners:</span> Banners added by you in the system. These can be any kind of banners as you are in charge of them.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Points to note:</span></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Excluding the banners added under any homepage collections, all the other banners (regardless if promotional or not), will be listed under the respective banner locations’ list of banners.</li>\r\n	<li>So, if a promotional banner is added by an advertiser and its location is set as the product detail page banner, this banner’s details will be visible in both the PPC Promotions Management list and the product detail page banner’s list (explained below).</li>\r\n	<li>This submodule lists all the banners that have been linked with this banner location, regardless of if they are promotional banners or banners added by you.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>You CANNOT delete a banner from the list.&nbsp;</div> '),(98,'MANAGE_NAVIGATIONS',-1,'Navigations','Configure which items appear and their order for both the header and footer navigation menus.','You cannot add a new navigation menu.','You can change the sequence of the page listed under the navigation panel, or add new links to under the navigation panel.','','\r\n<div>By default, there are 5 navigation menus added in the system.</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You can deactivate a navigation menu that you do not want to use, but you cannot delete any of these menus.</li>\r\n	<li>You cannot add a navigation menu to the list. However, you can edit the one already in the list, like changing the name and the items under it.</li>\r\n	<li>You can change the sequence of the page listed under the navigation panel, or add new links to them.<br />\r\n		\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>To change the sequence, click on the grey area and drag and drop the page link.</li>\r\n			<li>To add a new link, click on the Add icon. Enter the caption name, which is the text that will be displayed on the front end.</li>\r\n		</ul></li> \r\n	<li>You can add both onsite and offsite page links to the navigation panels. </li>\r\n</ul>    '),(99,'SHOPS_REPORT',-1,'Shops Sales Report','Detailed shop sales report that includes information on total sales, sold quantity, refunded orders, and total earnings made by the shop. ','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Apply filters from the advance search and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(104,'BUYERS_REPORT',-1,'Buyers Report','Detailed buyer report that includes information on the total purchase amount, available balance, received rewards, and more of each buyer. ','Apply filters from advance search and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The report has a few default columns. To include additional columns in the report, click on Columns and select the respective checkboxes. </li>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(105,'GETTING_STARTED',-1,'','','','','',''),(127,'MANAGE_SELLER_INVENTORIES',-1,'Seller\'s Product Inventories','View and edit each seller\'s products inventory details.','Each product variant\'s inventory details is listed here separately. ','Use the product\'s missing information icon to view the product\'s missing info due to which is it not being displayed at the front end. ','','\r\n<div>A product catalog is like a blueprint of the product, while the inventory details is the stocking details of the respective product.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Each seller can add inventory details for every master product variant available on the platform.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>A product can have multiple variants. For example, a shirt can be available in different colors (blue and black) and sizes (L and S). Hence, the shirt\'s variant types include - Black L, Black S, Blue L, and Blue S.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Each product variant\'s inventory details will be listed separately.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>There can be <span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">multiple inventory details</span> for the <span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">same product variant</span> but for <span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">different sellers</span>. This is because, different sellers are selling the same product in their store on the platform.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Use the product\'s missing information icon to see what info is missing of the product due to which it is not visible on the front end, even after its inventory details have been updated. Reasons can include - no tax category linked, no category linked, no brand linked, etc.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>   '),(175,'SETTINGS',-1,'System settings','Get started by configuring the platform settings by going through each section and update the settings accordingly.','','If you are not sure about any specific setting, please go through relevant section in user manual first before making changes.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Click on Labels to update all the labels on the platform.</li>\r\n	<li>Update the various commission rates through site commission and affiliate commission.</li>\r\n	<li>Set up various forms and email templates under SMS templates, Email templates, and Seller Approval Form.</li>\r\n	<li>Manage the shipping zones, countries, and states where your platform will be active.</li>\r\n	<li>You can always come back and change the settings under this module.</li>\r\n	<li>Use the search bar at the top to look for sections faster.</li>\r\n	<li>Turn on the maintenance mode toggle switch to notify the users that the site is currently down.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(177,'MANAGE_BADGE_REQUESTS',-1,'Badge Requests','Manage all the badges requested by sellers that they would like to link to their product, product variant or shop. ','The Seller cannot send multiple requests for a particular badge. Seller has to delete the previous requests if the seller wants to add more records in that badge.','Manual Badges require the approval of the admin (you) before they are used by sellers, while automatic badges don\'t require any approval.','','Badges are icons, logos or images that you can create under Promotion > Badges. These badges are made available to the sellers in order to build trust among buyers that visit the platform.&nbsp;<br />\r\n\r\n<ul><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Features:</span>\r\n	<li>Can only be created by Admin.</li>\r\n	<li>Badges created by you (admin) will be displayed to all the sellers under the Seller > Promotions > Badges.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>Based upon the source of generation (trigger type), Badges are classified into 2 types: Manual and Automatic.\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Manual Badges:</span>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>There are two kinds of Manual badges - open and closed.</div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Open manual badges can be assigned directly to a shop, product or product variant by the seller. </div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Close manual badges require the approval of the admin (you) before the seller can link them to their shop, product or product variant.</div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Defining time period for a manual badge is not mandatory.</div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div>Linking of a manual badge to a product, product variant or shop is mandatory. This can be done both by you or the seller.&nbsp;</div></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Automatic Badges:</span>\r\n	<li>These badges will be allotted to a shop or seller automatically once the shop or seller fulfills some predefined conditions that you (admin) define for the respective badge when creating it.</li>\r\n	<li>These badges cannot be assigned manually and do not require any approval.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<div><br />\r\n		</div>\r\n</ul> '),(178,'BLOG_POST_CATEGORIES',-1,'Blog Post Categories','Manage all the Blog Posts Categories displayed under Blog section at front end.','Categories are important to stack related content together making it easier for users to find what they are looking for.','Adjust the order of the Main/Root Categories as displayed at the front end using the drag and drop feature here. ','','\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>Every website needs a blog since it helps increase the platform’s visibility online. The more blog content you add to your platform, the more opportunities your website will have to show up in the top search engine results, including Google and Bing.&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div><br />\r\n		</div>\r\n	<div>A blog is a web page that you update on a regular basis. Oftentimes, brands have blogs right on their websites, making it easier for users to find and engage with your posts. Within your blog, you can share long-form articles that cover topics your target audience may want to read or learn about.</div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n			<div>By grouping all the related blog content under specific categories, you can help your audience find their desired content much faster. </div></li>\r\n		<li>\r\n			<div>These categories can be viewed on the upper-right corner of the blog page along with a search icon that allows the users to search for a specific blog category or blog post.</div></li>\r\n		<li>\r\n			<div>Add multiple subcategories and link them to a Main/Root Category.</div></li>\r\n		<li>\r\n			<div>Adjust the order of the Main/Root Categories as displayed at the front end using the drag and drop feature here.&nbsp;</div></li>\r\n	</ul><br />\r\n	</div>  '),(179,'MANAGE_IMPORT_INSTRUCTIONS',-1,'Import Instructions','Manage the import instructions for all the sections of the platform, which are reflected under the import/export module.','It is advised not to edit these instructions unless and until you are trying to make it easier to understand.','If you have made many changes and want to reset them, click the \"Reset to Default\" link in the form. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All the import instructions listed here are reflected under Import > Import/Export.</li> \r\n	<li>These instructions guide you through the process of how you can import the data.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>It is advised not to edit these instructions, so as to not cause any confusions later on.&nbsp;</div>  '),(180,'MANAGE_COLLECTIONS',-1,'Collections','Manage all the collections that make your website\'s homepage. Personalize and rearrange these sections as per your taste.','','Collections can be repeated as per your choice. You can choose different layouts for the same collection. ','','By default, the system will come with a few main collections already added to the list. You can edit these collections or delete them accordingly.<br />\r\n\r\n<div><br />\r\n	</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>Add collections to the layout, remove collections, deactivate/activate collections, define the collections and even change the order of the collections here.</div></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>There are 12 collection types that you can create. </li>\r\n	<li>To add a new collection, click on New. Select the collection type and its layout. Fill in the related form and select the items that you want to display in the collection. </li>\r\n	<li>To unpublish a collection from the front end, simply turn OFF the toggle switch beside the collection. You can also delete it.</li>\r\n	<li>Collections can only be created once you have added products, brands, and categories to the platform. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>   '),(183,'DISCOUNT_REPORT',-1,'Discount Coupon Reports','Discount coupon report on date the coupon was used, the discount amount, and more. ','Filters and selected columns will impact the exported data.','Apply filters from advance search and select relevant columns to view data and export the same.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Drag the headers under the Columns list to change the order of the columns.</li>\r\n	<li>Sort the report by clicking on a header. The highlighted header indicates that the column is sorted. And the direction of the arrow will indicate the sorting type.</li> \r\n	<li>Click on Export to download the adjusted report after sorting a header, adding columns, and changing the sequence of the columns, on a spreadsheet. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(184,'IMPORT_EXPORT',-1,'Import & Export','Perform bulk import or export for relevant data via CSV file.','Double-check interdependent data while importing CSV files.','Tweak import/export settings beforehand.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Export: Download the categories, users, products, etc., data in a separate CSV file from this platform as a backup, or to use it elsewhere.</li>\r\n	<li>Import: Add your data via exported CSV files. The instructions to import each type of data are explained on the first tab of each form. </li>\r\n	<li>Add Media to Server: Upload all media files on the platform\'s server under this section. This makes the image uploading process much simpler.</li>\r\n	<li>Settings: There are multiple settings that govern the import and export process. Configure these settings before you import or export any data so as to avoid any errors.</li>  \r\n	<li>Import instructions can be managed under CMS >> Import instructions.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(185,'MANAGE_SHIPPING_PROFILE',-1,'Shipping Profiles','Create and manage shipping profiles\' for products\' require special rates or that need to ship to different zones.','','','','\r\n'),(186,'MANAGE_PICKUP_ADDRESSES',-1,'Pickup Addresses','Setup pickup locations addresses along with delivery days and time slots for customers. ','Avoid creating a 24 hours slot timings for order pickup.','To configure pickup time slot display interval, please go to Settings > System Configuration > Checkout Tab.','','\r\n'),(187,'MANAGE_SHIPPED_PRODUCTS',-1,'Shipped Products','Track and manage your orders and shipment.','','','','\r\n'),(188,'METATAG_MANAGEMENT',-1,'Meta Tags Management','Define the meta information (metadata) for all the platform\'s pages.','Metadata, also called Meta Tags, is data that describes the data on the page.','Meta Tag consists of a page title and meta description for every page that shares a brief about its contents. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Update all the metadata, including the meta title, meta description, meta keywords and other meta content for each web page.</li> \r\n	<li>The pages are categorized into different sections allowing you to update and manage the metadata for each page easily.</li>\r\n	<li>Click on the edit icon beside the web page. A form will appear allowing you to update the metadata for that page.</li>\r\n	<li>The metadata added should be - findable, accessible, interoperable and reusable.</li>\r\n</ul>  '),(191,'DASHBOARD',-1,'Dashboard','Overview of the Sales stats, Analytics, Recent orders, Customers\' activities, Top-selling products, and many more.','','','','\r\n'),(192,'GENERAL_CONFIGURATION',-1,'System Configurations','Configure the general system settings that will govern most of the operations of the platform.','','To setup third-party APIs, refer to our third party API guides for step by step guidance.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To set up your website fast initially, update the settings under business profile, business logo, website commission, and email configuration.</li>\r\n	<li>Enable the website maintenance mode under the System tab, to let the users know that the website is currently down.</li>\r\n	<li>You can revisit the settings and update them according to your requirements at that time.</li>\r\n	<li>Once you have configured these settings, activate the required plugins.</li>\r\n</ul> '),(193,'MANAGE_PLUGINS',-1,'Plugins ','The platform comes integrated with multiple third-party APIs.','Use relevant (production or sandbox) keys while using any third-party API.','Some plugins are important for the system to run, while some plugins, when activated, will affect the system\'s manual settings.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Configure the available plugins to offer extra features on your website.</li>\r\n	<li>Some plugins are important for the platform to run smoothly. These include the regular payment method and payout plugins. </li>\r\n	<li>Plugins like the currency converter, SMS notification, social login, and push notification plugins help enhance the user experience. </li>\r\n	<li>To automate your tax calculations and shipping process, activate a sales tax service, a shipping service, and a shipment tracking service plugin. This will override the manual process setup. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(194,'MANAGE_PAGES_LANGUAGE_DATA_BLOCK',-1,'Page Language Data','Manage and update the page title, page summary, warnings, recommendations, and help section\'s content of various modules on the platform. ','You can only edit the content of pages on the admin\'s dashboard. ','This section was created to help you. You can add additional pointers to it for yourself, or a sub-user.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Every module on the platform has a help section along with some descriptions, tips, and warnings at the top of that page. All the content under these sections can be managed here.</li> \r\n	<li>These sections were created to help you navigate and use the platform easily. </li>\r\n	<li>It is advised not to change the content for any submodule under this section. This is so that you do not get confused later on. </li>\r\n	<li>Although, you can still add extra pointers that you feel will help you better or edit the sections as per your understanding. </li>\r\n</ul>     '),(195,'MANAGE_COUNTRIES',-1,'Countries','Manage the list of countries that will be visible under any country field all over the platform.','','To remove a country from the serviceable list, deactivate that country\'s entry.','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Manage the list of countries that will be visible under any country field all over the platform.</li> \r\n	<li>Activate the countries where you want to do business in. Only the active countries will be visible in the country list all over the platform. </li>\r\n	<li>Edit a country by clicking on the edit icon beside it.</li>\r\n	<li>Add a new country to the list using the New button.</li>\r\n	<li>You cannot delete a country from the list, although you can deactivate it if you do not want it to be visible in any of the country dropdown lists on the platform. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(196,'MANAGE_EMAIL_TEMPLATES',-1,'Email Templates','Manage system email templates','You cannot add a new email template. ','Admin can only modify the default email templates by adjusting body text, font size, color, logo, footer content etc.  ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Each template has a replacement variable kept inside curly brackets{}. </li>  \r\n	<li>When you send the email, text inside the brackets is replaced with information setup prior such as recipient\'s email address, website name, etc. </li>\r\n</ul> '),(197,'MANAGE_SELLER_APPROVAL_FORM',-1,'Seller Information Form','Insert custom fields in a Seller Sign Up form as per your requirement.\r\n\r\n','','Change label, mandatory field, field type, field order with easy add, edit, drag and drop options. ','','\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The added form fields will show up under the Activation Tab of the Seller Sign Up form.</li>\r\n</ul> '),(448,'MASTER_PRODUCT_REQUEST_FORM',-1,'Master Product Request','Update the Products information requested by Sellers to make it available under Master Catalog.','','','','\r\n'),(541,'ORDER_VIEW',-1,'Order Details','','','','','\r\n'),(563,'MANAGE_MESSAGES',-1,'Users Messages','View the message threads between buyers and seller.','','','','\r\n'),(580,'MANAGE_SELLER_PRODUCTS_REQUEST',-1,'Seller\'s Product Requests','Manage the status of new products requested by sellers to add them to their own catalog (seller catalog).','Seller products are available only for the respective seller once they approved.','Define if the seller has the option to add seller products or not under Settings > System Configuration > Product tab. ','','\r\n<div>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>A seller product is the product that is only available for the respective seller. It becomes a part of that respective seller\'s catalog. No other seller can add inventories for another seller\'s product.</li>\r\n		<li>Once you (admin) approve the seller\'s product request, the respective seller can add its inventory details and begin selling the same in their shop.&nbsp;</li>\r\n		<li>Allow or disallow the sellers to add their own products under&nbsp;Settings > System Configurations > Product Tab.</li>\r\n		<li>Activate the settings where sellers need the admin’s approval (your approval) before adding a product to their shop catalog under Settings > System Configurations > Product tab.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul></div>     '),(714,'MANAGE_SHIPPING_PACKAGES',-1,'Shipping Packages','Configure a shipping package container (cartons) dimensions that are used to ship items.','It is required to link shipping packages with products when the system enabled third-party shipping services (plugins).','Admin can enable/disable Product shipping packages from Settings >> System Configurations >> Product','','\r\n'),(920,'MANAGE_SMS_TEMPLATES',-1,'SMS Templates','Manage system-defined SMS templates.','You cannot add a new SMS template. ','Admin can only modify the default SMS templates by adjusting body text. ','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>Each template has a replacement variable kept inside curly brackets{}. </li>  \r\n	<li>When you send the SMS, text inside the brackets are replaced with the information setup prior such as user name, website name etc. </li>\r\n</ul>'),(925,'SOCIAL_PLATFORM',-1,'Social Platform','Add links, icons of your preferred social media profiles including Facebook, LinkedIn, Instagram, and more','','These social profile badges will show up on the website\'s home page footer area and in all outgoing system emails.','','\r\n<ul>  \r\n	<li>With the +Add button, you can instantly add a new social profile.</li>\r\n	<li>Each added profile will open in a new browser window.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(926,'MANAGE_REQUEST_FOR_QUOTE',-1,'Request For Quote','','','','',''),(927,'MANAGE_RFQ_OFFERS',-1,'Offers','','','','','');
